text: Katsiaryna Kulpo (born 23 December 1987) is a Belarusian synchronized swimmer. She competed in the women's duet at the 2008 Olympic Games with Nastassia Parfenava. Katsiaryna now works as an assistant coach for the Singapore synchronized swimming team. == References == Category:1987 births Category:Living people Category:Belarusian synchronized swimmers Category:Olympic synchronized swimmers of Belarus Category:Synchronized swimmers at the 2008 Summer Olympics
